# HOW_TO remote network capture using tcpdump and pipe the output to local wireshark


- creare una fifo
$> mkfifo <path/to/fifoName.fifo>

- lanciare wireshark in background
--- -k : Start the capture session immediately.
--- -n : Disable network object name resolution
--- -i : capture interface file
$> wireshark -kni <path/to/fifoName.fifo> &

- lanciare tcpdump remoto e salvare l'output nella fifo
--- -s 0 : snarf 0 bytes of data from each packet rather than the default of 262144 bytes
--- -n   : Don't convert addresses
--- -w - : log to stdout
--- -U   : as each packet is saved, it will be written to the output file
--- -i   : network interface
$> sshpass -p <passwd> ssh <name>@<address> 'tcpdump -s 0 -n -w - -U -i <interface>' >  <path/to/fifoName.fifo>
